Contributor License Agreement (CLA)
Contribution Guidelines

By contributing to ApexMQ, you agree to the following terms:

Original Work:
You confirm that your contribution is your own work, and that you have the right to submit it to the project.

Assigning Rights:
By submitting your code, you grant Benthara Gamage Kavindu Harshitha the right to use, distribute, and modify your contribution as part of the project, under the AGPL-3.0 license.

Clean Submission:
Your code should be clean and follow the repository’s standards. It should be submitted via Pull Requests (PRs) to the contributors branch or the relevant feature branch after discussion and approval of the feature request.

Feature Requests:
If you wish to propose a new feature, open an issue for discussion. Once the feature is approved, a specific branch will be created for you to submit your code.

Review Process:
All contributions will be reviewed. You must follow the project’s contribution workflow (fork the repository, create PRs, etc.).

Attribution:

Contributions will be attributed to the author, but ownership of the project remains with Benthara Gamage Kavindu Harshitha.

How to Contribute

Fork the repository on GitHub.
Create a new branch for your feature or bug fix.
Submit a Pull Request (PR) to the relevant branch, following the contribution guidelines above.
Your contribution will be reviewed and merged if it meets the project standards.

